WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:09.226
- Previously, on "Shooter"...

00:10.836 --> 00:10.880
- Atlas and the Swaggers
have been interlinked

00:11.707 --> 00:11.750
since the beginning.

00:12.186 --> 00:12.360
[gunshot]

00:13.317 --> 00:13.709
- Brooks killed my father.

00:14.971 --> 00:15.232
You're going to prison,
not the Supreme Court.

00:15.711 --> 00:16.625
- Swagger!

00:16.668 --> 00:18.148
- I run this country--me.

00:18.192 --> 00:20.063
Not you
and your goddamn cabal.

00:20.107 --> 00:22.413
- For decades,
presidents have told me

00:22.457 --> 00:23.675
the very same thing.

00:23.719 --> 00:25.634
- Must be Atlas operations HQ.

00:25.677 --> 00:28.332
- I came here to take out
the top of the food chain.

00:28.376 --> 00:30.465
[device beeping]

00:30.508 --> 00:31.466
[phone ringing]

00:31.509 --> 00:32.554
- Brooks is dead.

00:32.597 --> 00:34.556
There is no Atlas.

00:34.599 --> 00:36.732
You and I are not finished.
- I never said I was.

00:36.775 --> 00:38.690
- An event is imminent,
right here in D.C.

00:38.734 --> 00:41.432
I need you to find out
what it is and stop it.

00:41.476 --> 00:43.652
- You'll still have the problem
of these evil forces

00:43.695 --> 00:45.175
in the shadows.
- Unless you agree

00:45.219 --> 00:46.742
to shoulder the burden.

00:46.785 --> 00:48.135
- Sweetheart,
this is the last thing

00:48.178 --> 00:49.353
I need to do.
- I'm done.

00:49.397 --> 00:51.138
Mary needs
at least one parent.

00:51.181 --> 00:52.704
- Don't give up on us.
- This is just who you are.

00:52.748 --> 00:54.358
You're the man that runs
towards a bomb

00:54.402 --> 00:55.794
and not away from one.

00:55.838 --> 00:58.101
- If I'm willing
to make that sacrifice

00:58.145 --> 00:59.581
with my family,
what do you think

00:59.624 --> 01:01.452
I'd be willing to do to yours?

01:01.496 --> 01:03.280
- You do anything to them,
your body will hit the ground

01:03.324 --> 01:04.629
before you even hear a gunshot.

01:04.673 --> 01:06.327
- There's a 4-4 split
on the court.

01:06.370 --> 01:07.763
- Brooks would have
made it 5-4.

01:07.806 --> 01:09.852
Brooks dies.
- There is no backup nominee.

01:09.895 --> 01:11.375
- But 4-3 would still win it
for them.

01:11.419 --> 01:13.769
- They're gonna kill
a Supreme Court Justice.

01:13.812 --> 01:15.684
- He's been building
a bomb in here.

01:15.727 --> 01:17.251
What's his target?
- So, who's excited

01:17.294 --> 01:18.643
to go visit
the Supreme Court today?

01:18.687 --> 01:20.384
[all cheering]
- FBI!

01:20.428 --> 01:23.170
Evacuate the area!
- The explosion is a diversion

01:23.213 --> 01:24.432
to get the Justices evacuated.

01:24.475 --> 01:25.520
[device beeping]
- Shit.

01:25.563 --> 01:28.088
- Mom! Mom!

01:30.568 --> 01:32.266
- Where you going?
- Supreme Court!

01:32.309 --> 01:34.485
He's gonna pick up
his target there!

01:34.529 --> 01:35.486
- Nadine.

01:35.530 --> 01:37.271
♪

01:37.314 --> 01:40.709
- Justice, you've been ordered
to evacuate.

01:40.752 --> 01:42.145
- Let's go.

01:44.669 --> 01:47.411
[muffled sirens]

01:47.455 --> 01:50.284
[muffled speech]

01:50.327 --> 01:53.287
[tense music]

01:53.330 --> 02:00.381
♪

02:02.644 --> 02:04.428
- I'll go with her.
- [groaning]

02:04.472 --> 02:06.256
- I'll go with her.
- I--I'm not gonna be much help

02:06.300 --> 02:07.692
in a gunfight.
- Then don't get in one.

02:07.736 --> 02:09.607
Bob Lee doesn't need
a second gun,

02:09.651 --> 02:11.348
he needs someone to help him
navigate that building.

02:11.392 --> 02:13.742
- [groans]
Go.

02:13.785 --> 02:15.657
- Okay. All right.

02:15.700 --> 02:17.267
- [groans]

02:17.311 --> 02:19.574
You, too.
- Not a chance.

02:19.617 --> 02:22.577
[radio chatter]

02:22.620 --> 02:27.886
♪

02:27.930 --> 02:29.801
- This way, please.
Move toward the lawn.

02:29.845 --> 02:31.716
This way, this way!

02:31.760 --> 02:33.588
Towards the street, please.
Towards the lawn.

02:33.631 --> 02:35.198
Guys, this way.
This way please.

02:35.242 --> 02:36.547
- Not gonna work.

02:36.591 --> 02:38.201
If you try any
eyes-knees-groin,

02:38.245 --> 02:39.594
they're gonna think
you're the terrorist.

02:39.637 --> 02:40.812
- The bus was a decoy.

02:40.856 --> 02:42.292
I think the bomber
went this way.

02:42.336 --> 02:43.641
I gotta get in
to this building.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.295
You have any ideas?
- Yeah, follow me.

02:45.339 --> 02:46.688
- Move towards the lawn!

02:46.731 --> 02:48.211
This way, this way--
- Uh, excuse me, hi.

02:48.255 --> 02:49.691
We need to find, uh,
Henry Van Tassell.

02:49.734 --> 02:51.432
He's an aide to Justice Stewart.
- Can't do it.

02:51.475 --> 02:52.911
Building's being
evacuated, sir.

02:52.955 --> 02:54.478
- Yeah, that's the problem.
He called me

02:54.522 --> 02:56.001
about ten minutes ago
before the bomb went off

02:56.045 --> 02:58.308
He sounded scared; he said
he was in trouble--here.

02:58.352 --> 02:59.701
So, look, do what you gotta do,
we're gonna go look for him.

02:59.744 --> 03:01.006
- Hold on--
- Anybody of value

03:01.050 --> 03:02.312
has been evacuated okay?
- No, you guys--

03:02.356 --> 03:03.487
Keep the ID!
Keep it, okay?

03:03.531 --> 03:05.707
We're not the bad guys.
Thank you.

03:05.750 --> 03:07.535
It's a big place.

03:07.578 --> 03:09.537
- Where's the judges' chambers?
- This way, this way.

03:09.580 --> 03:10.842
Come on.

03:10.886 --> 03:11.843
♪

03:11.887 --> 03:12.844
[metal clanging]

03:12.888 --> 03:14.759
[man shouting]

03:14.803 --> 03:17.414
- Wait, what's that?

03:17.458 --> 03:20.243
[man moaning]
Shit...

03:20.287 --> 03:21.636
- [groans]
- What happened?

03:21.679 --> 03:23.681
You okay?
- My head...

03:23.725 --> 03:25.988
- Who did this?
- I didn't get a look at him,

03:26.031 --> 03:27.555
but I need to get
to Justice Gibson.

03:27.598 --> 03:29.034
- Why?
- [breathing heavily]

03:29.078 --> 03:31.559
- I'm her driver.

03:31.602 --> 03:34.562
[sinister music]

03:34.605 --> 03:36.520
♪

03:36.564 --> 03:38.914
- This is ridiculous.
- Ma'am?

03:38.957 --> 03:41.786
- Think we're outside
the blast radius yet?

03:41.830 --> 03:44.267
Turn around.
I have work to do.

03:44.311 --> 03:45.834
- The evacuation protocols
are very clear.

03:45.877 --> 03:48.402
- Don't talk to me
about protocol, young man.

03:48.445 --> 03:51.405
Protocol calls
for my regular driver.

03:51.448 --> 03:53.450
- Yes, ma'am.

03:53.494 --> 03:55.365
- Where are we going?
- Arlington.

03:55.409 --> 03:56.801
- Oh, good.

03:56.845 --> 03:59.021
I can stop by and say hello
to my husband.

03:59.064 --> 04:01.893
♪

04:01.937 --> 04:04.896
[siren chirping]

04:04.940 --> 04:11.990
♪

04:22.871 --> 04:24.046
[siren chirps]

04:33.490 --> 04:35.884
I'm not the Queen,
get out of my way.

04:35.927 --> 04:38.582
Ramiro, it's my lucky day.

04:38.626 --> 04:39.931
- Oh, is it?
- How's Dolores?

04:39.975 --> 04:41.933
- Oh, she's always worried,
you know.

04:41.977 --> 04:44.327
- Drag us out of our office
for nothing.

04:44.371 --> 04:46.373
- Okay, so we know
the evac location.

04:46.416 --> 04:48.331
What's the plan?
- Find a radio and call it in.

04:48.375 --> 04:49.637
- Uh, we can't.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.029
Coms are encrypted
during a terrorist event

04:51.073 --> 04:53.510
so nobody can listen in.

04:53.554 --> 04:55.120
What are you doing?
Where are you going?

04:55.164 --> 04:57.514
- Improvising.
- What--

04:57.558 --> 04:58.950
Are you gonna steal
this cop car?

04:58.994 --> 05:00.778
- Yup.
- What do I do?

05:00.822 --> 05:02.650
- Report me and tell them
where I went.

05:02.693 --> 05:04.869
- Okay.

05:04.913 --> 05:07.045
♪

05:07.089 --> 05:08.525
[tires squealing]

05:08.569 --> 05:11.528
[dramatic music]

05:11.572 --> 05:18.622
♪

05:21.190 --> 05:21.321
.

05:21.364 --> 05:24.454
[indistinct announcements
over PA]

05:25.281 --> 05:25.977
- Mr. Johnson.
- Yes.

05:26.500 --> 05:27.327
- Husband?
- Brother.

05:28.676 --> 05:29.851
- Okay, uh, she's stable,
but she's in bad shape.

05:29.894 --> 05:31.374
Shrapnel grazed
her carotid artery.

05:31.418 --> 05:33.245
And that's the good news,
'cause three millimeters

05:33.289 --> 05:34.508
to the right
and she would have died.

05:34.551 --> 05:36.161
- She awake?
- Uh, no.

05:36.205 --> 05:37.946
You're--you're welcome to stay.

05:37.989 --> 05:39.861
Uh, or if there's a change,
we can always try to call you,

05:39.904 --> 05:41.645
but as you can see, it's...
- I'll stay.

05:41.689 --> 05:43.995
- All right,
I'll let somebody know.

05:44.039 --> 05:45.867
- Yeah.
- Hey. News?

05:45.910 --> 05:48.173
She's stable now,
but touch-and-go earlier.

05:48.217 --> 05:49.349
- [sighs]
Jesus.

05:49.392 --> 05:50.959
Um, I'm on my way.

05:51.002 --> 05:52.482
I gotta walk,
every street is gridlocked.

05:52.526 --> 05:54.528
Looks like the target
was Justice Gibson.

05:54.571 --> 05:56.617
- They get her?
- Not yet.

05:56.660 --> 05:59.924
Bob Lee stole a police car
and is driving it to Arlington.

05:59.968 --> 06:02.405
He wanted me to tell you.

06:02.449 --> 06:04.189
Isaac?

06:04.233 --> 06:05.930
- I'm not going anywhere.

06:05.974 --> 06:07.410
- Tell Nadine
I'll see her soon.

06:07.454 --> 06:08.672
- Yeah.

06:08.716 --> 06:10.674
[phone beeps]

06:10.718 --> 06:13.068
[sighs]
- What's this for?

06:13.111 --> 06:15.070
- Swabbing for anthrax,
Justice Gibson.

06:15.113 --> 06:17.638
- My understanding
is it was a bomb, Corpsman.

06:17.681 --> 06:19.422
- Just a precaution.

06:19.466 --> 06:20.989
- Need your weapon
and your mobile.

06:21.032 --> 06:23.470
- I'm responsible
for the Justice's safety.

06:23.513 --> 06:26.386
- Not here.

06:29.084 --> 06:30.477
- I'm told you can
make personal calls

06:30.520 --> 06:32.435
from a secure line.
- Who would I call?

06:32.479 --> 06:34.524
I'd rather have a chat
with my colleagues.

06:34.568 --> 06:36.396
Where are we waiting?

06:36.439 --> 06:38.528
- Just down the corridor here,
ma'am.

06:38.572 --> 06:41.052
- You can stay here.

06:41.096 --> 06:43.315
[suspenseful music]

06:43.359 --> 06:47.058
- I'm just going
to go grab some paperwork.

06:47.102 --> 06:54.152
♪

07:51.775 --> 07:54.343
[dramatic music]

07:54.386 --> 07:56.476
[flare hissing]

07:56.519 --> 08:03.483
♪

08:06.181 --> 08:08.531
- Get into the safe room!

08:08.575 --> 08:15.625
♪

08:27.724 --> 08:29.813
- Shit.

08:29.857 --> 08:36.080
♪

08:37.604 --> 08:39.562
- Stop.

08:39.606 --> 08:41.651
Hands up.
- All right.

08:41.695 --> 08:45.046
I'm SWAT, I'm off-duty.
- ID, now.

08:45.089 --> 08:46.438
- Okay, it's in my wallet.

08:46.482 --> 08:50.268
I'm gonna reach for it.
- Slowly.

08:50.312 --> 08:57.362
♪

08:58.581 --> 09:02.150
♪

09:02.193 --> 09:04.587
- This way, please.
Everybody inside.

09:04.631 --> 09:08.548
♪

09:08.591 --> 09:10.680
[keypad beeping]

09:10.724 --> 09:13.596
♪

09:13.640 --> 09:18.253
- [gasps] Wow.

09:18.296 --> 09:21.386
Yeah, okay, now I'm scared.

09:21.430 --> 09:25.695
♪

09:25.739 --> 09:27.828
[monitors beeping]

09:27.871 --> 09:30.352
- [groans softly]

09:30.395 --> 09:32.789
♪

09:32.833 --> 09:34.574
- You don't look so bad
for someone

09:34.617 --> 09:36.227
who got shrapnel in their neck.

09:36.271 --> 09:39.840
- You look pretty bad
for someone who didn't.

09:39.883 --> 09:42.103
How's the kid?
- She's fine.

09:42.146 --> 09:44.235
You saved her.

09:44.279 --> 09:45.672
- She's lucky.

09:45.715 --> 09:49.371
- Bad shit is always
gonna happen, Nadine.

09:49.414 --> 09:52.766
How we respond to it,
that's what matters.

09:52.809 --> 09:55.159
They killed my wife,
I killed them.

09:55.203 --> 09:57.597
That was the wrong play.

09:57.640 --> 09:59.729
We gotta take this all the way.
- [chuckles]

09:59.773 --> 10:01.731
I'm not sure
there's anyone left, Isaac.

10:01.775 --> 10:04.908
- There's always someone.

10:04.952 --> 10:07.519
- So, what, you want
to take on the world?

10:07.563 --> 10:08.825
- Yeah.

10:08.869 --> 10:11.741
But in the right way.

10:11.785 --> 10:14.614
- You really want
to do this?

10:14.657 --> 10:16.659
Become Atlas?

10:16.703 --> 10:19.227
- POTUS practically engraved
the invitation.

10:19.270 --> 10:21.577
Like I told Gregson...

10:21.621 --> 10:23.492
Nature hates a vacuum.

10:23.535 --> 10:25.494
Somebody needs to fill it.

10:28.932 --> 10:30.717
- Where's Swagger?

10:30.760 --> 10:32.283
- He got a lead.

10:32.327 --> 10:34.372
Justice Gibson.

10:34.416 --> 10:36.287
- What--
what are you doing here?

10:36.331 --> 10:38.768
- Because if he fails,
they'll be here next.

10:38.812 --> 10:42.293
You're in no condition
to fight.

10:42.337 --> 10:43.643
- This reminds me
of that bomb threat

10:43.686 --> 10:45.209
from two years ago.

10:45.253 --> 10:46.776
At least that time
we were locked down

10:46.820 --> 10:48.691
in our chambers.

10:48.735 --> 10:50.171
I hate to say it,

10:50.214 --> 10:51.651
but there are worse places
to die.

10:51.694 --> 10:53.827
I'm proud of the work we do.

10:53.870 --> 10:55.872
Some nutball wants
to silence us,

10:55.916 --> 10:58.179
we must be
doing something right.

10:58.222 --> 11:01.182
[suspenseful music]

11:01.225 --> 11:02.487
♪

11:02.531 --> 11:03.750
- I need to see Justice Gibson.

11:03.793 --> 11:06.404
- No one in or out
till all-clear.

11:06.448 --> 11:08.755
♪

11:08.798 --> 11:11.235
- I'm not asking.

11:11.279 --> 11:14.238
[sinister music]

11:14.282 --> 11:21.332
♪

11:34.563 --> 11:39.524
♪

11:39.568 --> 11:42.571
- Don't touch him!

11:49.447 --> 11:50.971
- [gasps]

11:53.277 --> 11:55.845
[tense music]

11:55.889 --> 11:57.847
[siren wailing distantly]

11:57.891 --> 12:02.678
♪

12:02.722 --> 12:06.421
- Shit.

12:06.464 --> 12:09.032
[debris clattering]

12:09.076 --> 12:16.300
♪

12:18.520 --> 12:20.391
- He's got a suicide vest.

12:20.435 --> 12:22.785
- Jesus Christ.

12:22.829 --> 12:25.483
♪

12:25.527 --> 12:27.877
- Ramiro, the moment
he opens the door,

12:27.921 --> 12:29.444
he's gonna blow that thing.

12:29.487 --> 12:30.575
I don't think
a fire extinguisher's

12:30.619 --> 12:32.447
gonna help.

12:34.666 --> 12:39.410
♪

12:39.454 --> 12:40.934
- It's over.

12:40.977 --> 12:42.413
Atlas is dead!

12:42.457 --> 12:44.589
You're doing this
for nothing, man.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.417
[panel beeps]

12:46.461 --> 12:53.468
♪

12:54.643 --> 12:56.384
- [grunts]

12:56.427 --> 12:58.516
- Go, go, go!

12:58.560 --> 13:00.562
Go! Get out of here!

13:00.605 --> 13:02.999
♪

13:03.043 --> 13:06.350
[both men grunting]

13:06.394 --> 13:12.922
♪

13:12.966 --> 13:15.011
- [shrieks]

13:15.055 --> 13:22.062
♪

13:25.761 --> 13:27.850
[cries out]

13:27.894 --> 13:32.594
♪

13:38.643 --> 13:38.818
.

13:38.861 --> 13:41.690
- Homeland Security is set
to hold a press conference

13:41.733 --> 13:44.824
at 5:00 to address the atta--

13:45.999 --> 13:46.173
- He used to sleep
through mortar attacks

13:47.000 --> 13:48.088
at our base.
- [laughs]

13:48.131 --> 13:50.481
At least he doesn't snore.

13:50.525 --> 13:52.527
I see they kept your name
out of it.

13:52.570 --> 13:55.486
- Yeah, FBI felt
it would be too confusing.

13:55.530 --> 13:57.793
They went with
the less complicated version.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.187
- Hm. Lone nutjob, huh?

14:00.230 --> 14:03.103
- There was nothing
to connect him to Atlas.

14:03.146 --> 14:05.496
How are you?
- [chuckles]

14:05.540 --> 14:09.631
Couple of new battle scars,
but alive.

14:09.674 --> 14:10.850
And grateful.

14:13.548 --> 14:15.028
- You still planning
on taking over Atlas?

14:15.071 --> 14:17.900
- Not alone.

14:17.944 --> 14:21.556
- Ah, the dead rise.

14:21.599 --> 14:23.950
Atlas was a mistake.

14:23.993 --> 14:25.647
But there's always
gonna be someone

14:25.690 --> 14:27.083
trying to run things.
- Might as well

14:27.127 --> 14:28.302
be the good guys.

14:28.345 --> 14:29.999
- Is that you?

14:30.043 --> 14:31.696
- I think so.

14:31.740 --> 14:33.611
- Any word on Bama?

14:33.655 --> 14:35.918
- No, not yet.

14:35.962 --> 14:38.138
Where's Harris?
- Apparently he started

14:38.181 --> 14:41.837
a new job, and he brought me
flowers earlier.

14:41.881 --> 14:43.143
- [laughs]

14:43.186 --> 14:46.973
Classy.
- And Julie?

14:47.016 --> 14:49.976
- That's where I'm headed next.
- Smart man.

14:50.019 --> 14:52.761
- Once you get that squared,
we're accepting resumes.

14:52.804 --> 14:54.067
- [chuckles]

14:54.110 --> 14:56.852
It's tempting,
but I think I'll pass.

14:56.896 --> 14:58.680
I wanna focus
on saving my marriage

14:58.723 --> 14:59.899
instead of the world.

14:59.942 --> 15:01.944
- She'll be happy to see you.

15:01.988 --> 15:04.860
- We'll see.

15:04.904 --> 15:06.862
Take care of yourself.

15:06.906 --> 15:09.169
Both of you.

15:09.212 --> 15:11.171
Shit gets weird out there.

15:11.214 --> 15:15.131
[mellow music]

15:15.175 --> 15:17.873
- Red, thanks for coming.

15:17.917 --> 15:19.353
- I didn't come
to see you, pissant.

15:19.396 --> 15:22.617
Where is he?
- Camp David.

15:22.660 --> 15:25.837
Asked me to speak with you.
- Did he?

15:25.881 --> 15:29.015
- Wanted me to thank you
for your service.

15:29.058 --> 15:30.625
- Hmm.

15:30.668 --> 15:32.061
My resignation.

15:32.105 --> 15:34.368
You gotta be shitting me.
- I'd offer you pancakes,

15:34.411 --> 15:36.196
but pretty sure
the commissary's

15:36.239 --> 15:38.285
done serving breakfast.
- I want to talk to POTUS, now.

15:38.328 --> 15:40.374
- He's spending the weekend
with his wife.

15:40.417 --> 15:43.986
Do-not-disturb kind of thing,
if you know what I mean.

15:44.030 --> 15:46.032
- Enjoy your small victory,
Downey.

15:46.075 --> 15:47.772
I'll be back.

15:47.816 --> 15:51.124
- That's, uh, Deputy Chief
of Staff Downey, Red.

15:51.167 --> 15:53.039
And I doubt it.

15:53.082 --> 15:54.997
Uh, the president
has actually asked me

15:55.041 --> 15:56.912
to have
the Department of Labor

15:56.956 --> 15:59.219
look into the use
of undocumented immigrants

15:59.262 --> 16:00.742
in meat packing plants.

16:00.785 --> 16:02.744
Specifically, in Texas.

16:02.787 --> 16:06.400
Says they should go back
30 years if they have to.

16:06.443 --> 16:10.621
- I will burn this whole place
to the ground, young man.

16:10.665 --> 16:13.189
- With what?

16:13.233 --> 16:14.408
Look around, Red.

16:14.451 --> 16:17.759
You don't have
any friends left.

16:17.802 --> 16:19.065
Make sure you leave
your government ID

16:19.108 --> 16:23.069
with the Secret Service
on your way out.

16:23.112 --> 16:26.072
[bright, tense music]

16:26.115 --> 16:33.122
♪

16:37.648 --> 16:38.867
Yeah.

16:39.781 --> 16:41.783
♪

16:44.394 --> 16:47.093
- Hey, you're home.

16:48.877 --> 16:50.400
I'm so glad you're safe.

16:53.838 --> 16:56.189
- Where's Mary?
- She's with Anne.

16:56.232 --> 16:58.104
They'll be back later.

16:58.147 --> 17:00.062
She's missed you like crazy.

17:00.106 --> 17:01.977
- Yeah, we--

17:03.239 --> 17:06.460
[tense music]

17:06.503 --> 17:08.810
- Look, I'm--
I'm glad that you're home,

17:08.853 --> 17:11.160
but we still need to talk.

17:11.204 --> 17:14.120
- What is all this?

17:14.163 --> 17:17.775
- I don't know what to do.

17:17.819 --> 17:19.255
- Baby, I don't want you
to leave.

17:19.299 --> 17:20.996
- I know that,
but what about everything

17:21.040 --> 17:22.389
with your dad?

17:22.432 --> 17:24.826
- It's done, it's over.
- Are you sure?

17:24.869 --> 17:27.176
- The man who killed my father
is dead.

17:27.220 --> 17:30.092
- And what about Atlas?
- Atlas is finished.

17:30.136 --> 17:31.920
Isaac and Nadine
are working some angle,

17:31.963 --> 17:34.009
but it has nothing
to do with me.

17:34.053 --> 17:37.839
- I don't--I don't know how
to trust you anymore.

17:37.882 --> 17:39.841
I just don't.

17:39.884 --> 17:44.150
♪

17:44.193 --> 17:47.022
- That's fair.

17:47.066 --> 17:51.244
♪

17:51.287 --> 17:54.986
But before you make
a decision about us,

17:55.030 --> 17:57.163
there is one thing left to do,
and I need you and Mary

17:57.206 --> 18:00.166
by my side to do it.

18:00.209 --> 18:02.385
♪

18:02.429 --> 18:06.041
- This would have made Sam
and your daddy both happy.

18:06.085 --> 18:07.477
- I agree.
- Don't you want

18:07.521 --> 18:09.175
to say something?

18:09.218 --> 18:11.786
- Kinda think I've said
all I can say, Mouse.

18:11.829 --> 18:15.137
- But this is the last time
we're gonna see them.

18:17.835 --> 18:19.924
- You're right.

18:22.318 --> 18:25.191
These two men raised me, Mary.

18:25.234 --> 18:28.150
They both taught me
everything I know.

18:28.194 --> 18:30.805
Right from wrong,
good from bad.

18:30.848 --> 18:34.069
I loved and respected
both of them in different ways.

18:34.113 --> 18:37.159
- Was Grandpa Earl a good dad?

18:37.203 --> 18:39.074
Like you?

18:39.118 --> 18:41.511
- He did the best he could.

18:41.555 --> 18:43.905
Grandpa had a secret--

18:43.948 --> 18:46.081
something that made him
feel bad--

18:46.125 --> 18:50.390
and sometimes that bad feeling
came out as anger.

18:50.433 --> 18:53.175
I never wanted to be that way.

18:53.219 --> 18:55.221
♪

18:55.264 --> 18:58.049
That's over now.

18:58.093 --> 19:01.444
Sam helped bring
my daddy some peace...

19:01.488 --> 19:04.578
and some peace to us too.

19:04.621 --> 19:07.581
[mellow music]

19:07.624 --> 19:09.017
♪

19:09.060 --> 19:10.192
- You ready?

19:10.236 --> 19:12.194
Okay.

19:12.238 --> 19:19.201
♪

19:19.245 --> 19:22.204
[thunder rumbles]

19:22.248 --> 19:29.255
♪

19:36.305 --> 19:39.047
- Hey.

19:39.090 --> 19:40.875
Ignore him, all right?

19:40.918 --> 19:44.835
- Just give me a minute.

19:44.879 --> 19:47.838
[tense music]

19:47.882 --> 19:54.932
♪

19:57.500 --> 20:00.286
Unless you're here to confess
to arranging my daddy's murder,

20:00.329 --> 20:03.071
you best leave.

20:03.114 --> 20:05.595
- I came to tell you
this fight is over.

20:05.639 --> 20:08.250
I'm selling the cattle company
and walking away.

20:08.294 --> 20:10.644
From all of it.
- Bullshit.

20:10.687 --> 20:13.037
- Swagger, you beat me.

20:13.081 --> 20:15.388
I've lost everything
that was ever important to me,

20:15.431 --> 20:17.172
including my son.

20:17.216 --> 20:20.262
- All of it was your choice.
- And so was this.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.308
I'm gone.

20:22.351 --> 20:24.484
I just don't want to spend
the rest of my life waiting

20:24.527 --> 20:26.616
for one of your bullets.

20:26.660 --> 20:28.270
- Then leave Texas.

20:28.314 --> 20:30.272
Don't come back.

20:30.316 --> 20:31.926
You don't deserve
to stand on the same ground

20:31.969 --> 20:35.582
my dad's buried in.

20:35.625 --> 20:40.891
♪

20:46.070 --> 20:46.462
.

20:46.506 --> 20:48.638
- I see you've been busy.
- It is amazing what you can do

20:49.378 --> 20:50.336
with a no-limit Amex.

20:50.379 --> 20:52.860
Signed a lease,
made it official.

20:52.903 --> 20:54.949
- What are we calling it?

20:54.992 --> 20:57.343
- "Prometheus."

20:57.386 --> 20:59.910
- You realize he was tortured
for helping humanity, right?

20:59.954 --> 21:01.825
- Thought it fit.

21:01.869 --> 21:04.132
We're gonna need some staff
and a CEO.

21:04.175 --> 21:06.961
- That gonna be you, Captain?
- I do have the experience.

21:07.004 --> 21:10.660
- Ah, but, uh,
I have the money.

21:10.704 --> 21:12.619
- Okay, so, partners?

21:12.662 --> 21:14.403
Fifty-fifty?

21:14.447 --> 21:16.884
- I handle the politics,
you handle the missions.

21:16.927 --> 21:18.929
- Works for me.

21:22.672 --> 21:24.587
- What's that?
- No idea.

21:24.631 --> 21:26.110
- Anyone else have keys
to this place?

21:26.154 --> 21:27.938
- There is no key,
it's digital.

21:27.982 --> 21:31.072
- Present from Red?

21:31.115 --> 21:34.075
[tense music]

21:34.118 --> 21:41.343
♪

21:48.785 --> 21:51.092
What is it?

21:51.135 --> 21:53.703
- It's the hard drive
from the Atlas campus.

21:53.747 --> 21:56.358
This is a complete record
of everything they ever did.

21:56.402 --> 21:58.839
- Holy shit.

21:58.882 --> 22:00.971
Looks like Carlita
made it out after all.

22:01.015 --> 22:03.452
- Not sure
if that's good or bad.

22:03.496 --> 22:04.975
- Guess we'll find out.

22:05.019 --> 22:07.064
♪

22:10.981 --> 22:14.158
- Jules?

22:14.202 --> 22:18.032
What are you doing, honey?
- Finishing the packing.

22:18.075 --> 22:19.512
- Where's Mouse?

22:19.555 --> 22:22.558
- She's at Anne's hotel
with her.

22:22.602 --> 22:24.038
- Please, Jules, let's just--
- Look, baby,

22:24.081 --> 22:26.910
this isn't gonna work, okay?
- Why not?

22:26.954 --> 22:28.651
- Because I saw the way
that you looked at Red.

22:28.695 --> 22:30.653
I know what you want to do.
- Julie, it's over.

22:30.697 --> 22:32.046
- He's leaving town.
- But you don't want it

22:32.089 --> 22:34.396
do be over, do you?
- Yes, I do!

22:34.440 --> 22:36.093
- So you're just gonna
let the man who's responsible

22:36.137 --> 22:37.965
for your father's death
walk away?

22:38.008 --> 22:40.489
Come on, Bob Lee,
you are who you are.

22:40.533 --> 22:42.578
- I am still the man
you fell in love with, Julie.

22:42.622 --> 22:44.972
I haven't changed.
- I have.

22:45.015 --> 22:46.930
I've changed.

22:46.974 --> 22:49.672
[somber music]

22:49.716 --> 22:52.153
- So you don't love me anymore.

22:52.196 --> 22:54.808
- I will never stop
loving you.

22:54.851 --> 22:56.200
- Then don't leave!
- I just don't

22:56.244 --> 22:57.941
love this anymore.

22:57.985 --> 23:00.030
- It's gonna change, I promise!
- Look, thank you

23:00.074 --> 23:01.641
for saying that,

23:01.684 --> 23:03.077
but we both know
that's not true.

23:03.120 --> 23:04.644
- You know that
there is nothing

23:04.687 --> 23:06.646
more important to me
than you and Mary.

23:06.689 --> 23:08.430
Nothing.

23:08.474 --> 23:10.650
- I do know that.

23:10.693 --> 23:13.217
But our lives have revolved
around you for so long.

23:13.261 --> 23:15.655
We need a break.

23:15.698 --> 23:17.874
[sighs]

23:17.918 --> 23:19.702
- Just a break?

23:19.746 --> 23:23.097
- I don't want a divorce.

23:23.140 --> 23:26.274
I don't, but...

23:26.317 --> 23:28.015
I don't know--
we need a reset.

23:28.058 --> 23:30.713
Something.

23:30.757 --> 23:32.628
- Then I'll leave.

23:32.672 --> 23:34.848
This is Mary's home.

23:34.891 --> 23:37.981
I wanna know
that the two of you are here.

23:38.025 --> 23:40.114
- We'll figure this out, okay?

23:42.986 --> 23:44.597
I'll tell Mary
when she comes home.

23:44.640 --> 23:46.599
- No.

23:46.642 --> 23:48.209
I want it to come from me.

23:48.252 --> 23:50.690
I don't want her to think
any of this is your fault.

23:50.733 --> 23:53.780
'Cause it's not.

23:53.823 --> 23:56.783
I'll get my things.

23:56.826 --> 24:02.832
♪

24:04.138 --> 24:07.968
- Crazy to think
that a lifetime worth of work

24:08.011 --> 24:10.231
can be undone with a signature.

24:10.274 --> 24:12.842
Cayman accounts set up?

24:12.886 --> 24:16.803
- As instructed.
- Excellent.

24:16.846 --> 24:19.632
Well, then we're done.

24:19.675 --> 24:21.677
[knocking on door]

24:21.721 --> 24:25.855
Have him come in
the back way, honey.

24:25.899 --> 24:29.642
It might be better
if you left now, Mark.

24:34.560 --> 24:36.649
[sighs]

24:36.692 --> 24:39.652
[foreboding music]

24:39.695 --> 24:42.524
♪

24:42.568 --> 24:45.309
You have an excellent
reputation, Prosada.

24:45.353 --> 24:47.268
♪

24:47.311 --> 24:50.271
What do they call you
back home in Colombia?

24:50.314 --> 24:53.666
- El Carnicero.
- The Butcher.

24:53.709 --> 24:56.538
I'm a butcher as well...

24:56.582 --> 24:59.759
and when people pay me
for meat, I deliver.

24:59.802 --> 25:01.674
- [chuckles]

25:01.717 --> 25:04.111
You will have what you desire.

25:04.154 --> 25:11.205
♪

25:13.250 --> 25:15.818
- Hundred now,
hundred when it's done.

25:15.862 --> 25:18.299
Split it any way you want.

25:18.342 --> 25:20.823
- Just Swagger?

25:20.867 --> 25:22.695
- Whoever's there.

25:22.738 --> 25:25.045
No witnesses.

25:25.088 --> 25:27.743
♪

25:27.787 --> 25:31.051
- As you wish.

25:31.094 --> 25:35.925
♪

25:40.713 --> 25:43.716
[solemn music]

25:43.759 --> 25:49.330
♪

25:49.373 --> 25:52.072
- I don't know how long.

25:52.115 --> 25:54.074
- You always go away, Dad.

25:54.117 --> 25:56.337
And you always come back.

25:56.380 --> 25:58.078
- Yeah.

25:58.121 --> 26:01.255
This time's
a little different.

26:01.298 --> 26:03.910
Mom and Dad
need some time apart.

26:03.953 --> 26:06.303
I'm not going on a mission.

26:06.347 --> 26:10.394
- Where are you going?

26:10.438 --> 26:12.962
- I'm gonna get a place nearby.

26:13.006 --> 26:16.226
- Why?

26:16.270 --> 26:17.880
- 'Cause we're gonna
live separate

26:17.924 --> 26:20.013
for a little while.

26:20.056 --> 26:21.318
- What?

26:21.362 --> 26:23.930
- Not--not forever, sweetie.

26:23.973 --> 26:27.281
Just until we get
some things figured out.

26:27.324 --> 26:31.677
- 'Cause you and Mom
have been fighting?

26:31.720 --> 26:32.939
- No.

26:32.982 --> 26:34.897
[phone buzzing]

26:34.941 --> 26:36.769
Not a good time, Sheriff.

26:36.812 --> 26:39.946
- You expecting
any VIPs today?

26:39.989 --> 26:41.469
- Why?
- Just clocked

26:41.512 --> 26:42.949
a low-flying helicopter.

26:42.992 --> 26:44.690
landed not too far
from your ranch.

26:44.733 --> 26:46.474
- All right, send everybody
you got to the ranch.

26:46.517 --> 26:49.303
Anne, I need you to take Mary
and get out of here.

26:49.346 --> 26:51.044
- What's going on?
- I think something's up.

26:51.087 --> 26:53.089
Uh, can you just take her
to the Sheriff's office

26:53.133 --> 26:55.701
and wait there?
I'll call you as soon as I can.

26:55.744 --> 26:57.093
- Come on, Mary.
We're gonna go run

26:57.137 --> 26:59.269
a little errand.
- What about Dad?

26:59.313 --> 27:00.836
- Uh, I'll see you soon,
sweetheart.

27:00.880 --> 27:02.055
I gotta go check on Mommy,
all right?

27:02.098 --> 27:04.144
- Yeah. Come on, sweetheart.

27:04.187 --> 27:07.060
[foreboding music]

27:07.103 --> 27:10.019
♪

27:10.063 --> 27:12.369
[turns key]

27:12.413 --> 27:14.981
Oh, shit.

27:15.024 --> 27:22.031
♪

27:40.833 --> 27:41.268
.

27:41.311 --> 27:42.661
[suspenseful music]

27:43.400 --> 27:45.185
[line ringing]

27:45.228 --> 27:46.795
[water running]

27:49.537 --> 27:50.930
[line ringing]

27:50.973 --> 27:52.801
- This is Julie.
You know what to do.

27:52.845 --> 27:54.934
[voicemail beeps]

27:54.977 --> 28:02.202
♪

28:28.837 --> 28:31.535
[bullets whizzing]

28:40.196 --> 28:42.416
[keypad beeping]

28:42.459 --> 28:49.510
♪

28:53.340 --> 28:56.386
- [panting]

29:00.869 --> 29:04.003
♪

29:04.046 --> 29:06.919
[tires squealing]

29:06.962 --> 29:14.230
♪

29:39.690 --> 29:40.996
[rapid gunfire]

29:41.040 --> 29:42.868
[bullets whining]

29:42.911 --> 29:49.918
♪

30:18.642 --> 30:19.948
- [exclaims]

30:19.992 --> 30:27.042
♪

30:40.099 --> 30:42.623
[bullets whining]

30:42.666 --> 30:49.673
♪

30:52.502 --> 30:54.374
[keypad beeping]

30:54.417 --> 30:58.117
- 9-1-1,
what's your emergency?

30:58.160 --> 30:59.466
Hello?

30:59.509 --> 31:06.473
♪

31:09.737 --> 31:11.130
- Shit.

31:11.173 --> 31:18.398
♪

31:41.029 --> 31:43.684
[siren wailing]

31:43.727 --> 31:45.512
- 9-1-1 says they've got
an open line

31:45.555 --> 31:46.948
at the Swagger ranch.

31:46.992 --> 31:47.993
Sounds like a hell
of a gunfight.

31:48.036 --> 31:49.646
- All hands on deck.

31:49.690 --> 31:51.387
Call Testa and have his men
back us up.

31:51.431 --> 31:58.481
♪

32:02.659 --> 32:04.748
- [cries out]

32:04.792 --> 32:07.099
[siren wailing]

32:07.142 --> 32:14.410
♪

32:23.028 --> 32:24.725
- [grunts]

32:24.768 --> 32:27.989
- [moans]

32:28.033 --> 32:29.991
[exclaims]

32:30.035 --> 32:31.645
♪

32:31.688 --> 32:33.560
- Bitch.

32:33.603 --> 32:35.127
- [grunts]

32:35.170 --> 32:37.042
- You gotta be prepared, puta.

32:37.085 --> 32:40.697
This ain't no bullshit.

32:40.741 --> 32:42.482
Bulletproof.

32:42.525 --> 32:44.832
Bad luck.
- Is this bulletproof?

32:44.875 --> 32:46.747
- [grunts]

32:46.790 --> 32:53.797
♪

33:41.280 --> 33:44.283
[tense music]

33:44.326 --> 33:45.806
♪

33:45.849 --> 33:47.895
- Julie!
- Bob Lee!

33:47.938 --> 33:48.939
- Julie!

33:48.983 --> 33:50.724
- Bob Lee!
I'm in here!

33:50.767 --> 33:52.247
- Baby!
- [gasping, groaning]

33:52.291 --> 33:54.554
[screams in pain]

33:54.597 --> 33:57.644
- Are there any more?
- No, just two dead.

33:57.687 --> 33:59.037
[groans]
- Holy shit.

33:59.080 --> 34:01.039
Good hunting, babe.
- Where's Mary?

34:01.082 --> 34:02.736
- She's with Anne
and she's safe.

34:02.779 --> 34:03.998
- [gasps, groans]

34:04.042 --> 34:05.086
- Let me see that,
let me see.

34:05.130 --> 34:07.306
- [groans]

34:07.349 --> 34:08.959
- All right, it went
all the way through.

34:09.003 --> 34:10.613
That's good, that's good.
- [gasping]

34:10.657 --> 34:12.833
- You're gonna be okay.
- Baby, I'm sorry.

34:12.876 --> 34:15.053
I'm sorry I lost faith in us
and in you.

34:15.096 --> 34:16.837
- Come on, don't think
about that right now.

34:16.880 --> 34:19.970
- Bob Lee!
- We're in here, Sheriff!

34:20.014 --> 34:22.321
We need an EMT, but we're okay.

34:22.364 --> 34:26.238
Hey, make sure we got 'em all.
- Done!

34:26.281 --> 34:27.935
- No, no, no,
let's wait for a stretcher.

34:27.978 --> 34:29.632
- No, I wanna
get the hell out of here.

34:29.676 --> 34:31.808
- Okay, all right.
Let me help you, come here.

34:31.852 --> 34:33.984
- [gasping]
- You're gonna be okay.

34:34.028 --> 34:36.161
I'm so sorry, baby.
- It's okay.

34:36.204 --> 34:39.686
[both breathing heavily]

34:39.729 --> 34:42.210
- It would have been better
if I just left it alone.

34:42.254 --> 34:44.125
My dad let
this life consume him.

34:44.169 --> 34:47.346
I'm not gonna be like that.

34:47.389 --> 34:50.958
I love you, and I love Mary.
- [gasping]

34:51.001 --> 34:53.178
This is my life.

34:53.221 --> 34:55.658
- I love you too, baby.

34:55.702 --> 34:58.661
[sirens wailing]

34:58.705 --> 35:01.664
[somber music]

35:01.708 --> 35:08.671
♪

35:08.715 --> 35:12.153
[indistinct chatter]

35:12.197 --> 35:14.895
- We're all clear, Sheriff.
- God damn.

35:14.938 --> 35:17.158
It was a hell of a day.

35:17.202 --> 35:19.334
♪

35:19.378 --> 35:22.337
[foreboding music]

35:22.381 --> 35:29.605
♪

35:32.217 --> 35:34.306
- All right...
- No.

35:34.349 --> 35:36.917
No, your dad's gun.
- I don't care about that.

35:36.960 --> 35:39.049
- I do.

35:39.093 --> 35:45.795
♪

35:45.839 --> 35:48.189
[bullet whining]

35:48.233 --> 35:49.625
- No!

35:49.669 --> 35:53.020
No, no!

35:53.063 --> 35:55.631
Julie! No, no, no!

35:55.675 --> 35:58.243
No! God, no!

35:58.286 --> 35:59.766
No!

35:59.809 --> 36:01.333
No, baby, no!

36:01.376 --> 36:03.335
No! Help!

36:03.378 --> 36:05.250
Help!

36:05.293 --> 36:07.339
Help!

36:07.382 --> 36:09.297
Baby, don't leave me.
Don't leave me, baby.

36:09.341 --> 36:11.778
Don't leave me!

36:11.821 --> 36:14.781
[whispering indistinctly]

36:14.824 --> 36:16.086
Julie...

36:16.130 --> 36:19.916
[whispering indistinctly]

36:19.960 --> 36:20.917
I'm sorry.

36:20.961 --> 36:22.005
♪

36:27.620 --> 36:27.837
.

36:27.881 --> 36:29.839
- How'd it go?
- As expected.

36:30.579 --> 36:31.189
Package got delivered.

36:31.667 --> 36:32.581
The new guy did well.

36:33.887 --> 36:34.322
- It's gonna take me
the better part of a year

36:35.715 --> 36:36.629
to get through all
this Atlas stuff and undo it.

36:39.284 --> 36:41.808
- Any word from Bob Lee?
- No, he's been off the grid

36:41.851 --> 36:43.723
since Julie's funeral.

36:43.766 --> 36:46.900
Got around-the-clock security
on Mary and the sister-in-law.

36:46.943 --> 36:49.816
Nothing out of the ordinary.
- He'll resurface, trust me.

36:49.859 --> 36:51.513
[knocking on door]

36:51.557 --> 36:52.775
- Excuse me?

36:52.819 --> 36:55.256
Uh, I have
a Harris Downey here?

36:55.300 --> 36:57.824
- Send him in.

36:57.867 --> 36:59.782
- [chuffs]
What's he want?

36:59.826 --> 37:01.915
- No idea.

37:01.958 --> 37:03.569
- Want me to stay?

37:03.612 --> 37:05.310
- Knowing Harris, he probably
wants to talk

37:05.353 --> 37:06.702
about our relationship.

37:06.746 --> 37:08.748
Yeah, please stay.

37:08.791 --> 37:10.358
- Have fun.

37:10.402 --> 37:12.534
- Uh--
[scoffs]

37:14.449 --> 37:18.410
- "HD."
- Isaac.

37:18.453 --> 37:21.282
He is still so friendly.
- He is who he is.

37:21.326 --> 37:22.675
It's reliable.

37:22.718 --> 37:24.372
- Hi.

37:24.416 --> 37:26.461
- So how's
the Deputy Chief of Staff?

37:26.505 --> 37:28.898
- Short on time,
especially since, technically,

37:28.942 --> 37:30.900
I'm not even here.

37:30.944 --> 37:32.511
The president's impressed.

37:32.554 --> 37:35.296
He appreciates the way
you cleaned up,

37:35.340 --> 37:36.776
didn't make a thing out of it.

37:36.819 --> 37:41.259
Wanted to know if you'd
take a look at that.

37:41.302 --> 37:44.523
- We're pretty busy.
- The president's asking.

37:44.566 --> 37:45.828
Personally.

37:45.872 --> 37:48.266
- [sighs]

37:48.309 --> 37:51.269
[tense music]

37:51.312 --> 37:52.966
♪

37:53.009 --> 37:55.621
Jesus.
- Christophe Schneizer.

37:55.664 --> 37:57.187
German nationalist.

37:57.231 --> 37:58.798
- Isn't it easier
just to say "Nazi"?

37:58.841 --> 38:00.234
- Mm.

38:00.278 --> 38:01.888
- And why would he
be helping ISIL?

38:01.931 --> 38:03.672
- He wants to be Chancellor.

38:03.716 --> 38:06.240
Figures if he makes Merkel
look bad...

38:06.284 --> 38:08.938
- [scoffs]
You don't need us for this.

38:08.982 --> 38:10.418
You've got the resources

38:10.462 --> 38:11.811
of the entire
Federal government.

38:11.854 --> 38:14.857
- I do, and they all
have names and fingerprints.

38:14.901 --> 38:17.469
Germany's an ally.
- Well, tell the Germans

38:17.512 --> 38:19.558
to deal with it.

38:19.601 --> 38:21.342
Of course.

38:21.386 --> 38:23.910
Then they would know that
you've been spying on them.

38:23.953 --> 38:25.390
- I'm glad to see
we can still finish

38:25.433 --> 38:27.522
each other's sentences.

38:27.566 --> 38:29.655
Discretion's paramount.

38:29.698 --> 38:31.004
You look great.

38:31.047 --> 38:32.701
The job suits you.

38:32.745 --> 38:34.921
- Harris.

38:34.964 --> 38:37.793
If I do this...

38:37.837 --> 38:40.666
you owe me.

38:45.235 --> 38:47.673
- What'd he want?

38:47.716 --> 38:50.371
- Just wanted to make sure
we knew the president

38:50.415 --> 38:52.678
appreciated our work.
- That's it?

38:52.721 --> 38:54.810
Could have called.
- Eh, what can I say?

38:54.854 --> 38:57.509
He likes me.

38:57.552 --> 39:00.512
[tense music]

39:00.555 --> 39:07.606
♪

39:13.786 --> 39:16.876
[wind howling]

39:36.591 --> 39:38.376
- [sighs]

39:38.419 --> 39:40.378
[meat clatters]

39:45.034 --> 39:47.602
[phone ringing]

39:50.083 --> 39:52.564
[phone continues to ring]

39:52.607 --> 39:55.567
[suspenseful music]

39:55.610 --> 40:02.661
♪

40:04.793 --> 40:07.535
- I wondered
if you'd find me.

40:07.579 --> 40:09.494
- I told you
if you ever touched my family

40:09.537 --> 40:11.626
I would never stop looking.

40:11.670 --> 40:18.720
♪

40:21.549 --> 40:24.030
- Don't suppose I can talk you
out of this.

40:24.073 --> 40:25.510
- No.

40:25.553 --> 40:27.033
You can't.

40:27.076 --> 40:29.601
♪

40:38.523 --> 40:40.612
[wind howling]

40:40.655 --> 40:43.615
♪ [Eddie Vedder's
"Long Night"]

40:43.658 --> 40:48.402
♪

40:48.446 --> 40:51.361
- ♪ Have no fear

40:51.405 --> 40:55.714
♪ For when I'm alone

40:55.757 --> 41:00.501
♪ I'll be better off

41:00.545 --> 41:04.374
♪ Than I was before

41:04.418 --> 41:08.988
♪ I've got this life

41:09.031 --> 41:13.514
♪ I'll be around to grow

41:13.558 --> 41:17.866
♪ Who I was before

41:17.910 --> 41:21.783
♪ I cannot recall

41:21.827 --> 41:24.786
♪ Long nights

41:24.830 --> 41:28.442
♪ Allow me to feel

41:28.486 --> 41:30.009
♪ I'm falling

41:30.052 --> 41:31.793
♪ I am falling

41:31.837 --> 41:35.884
♪ The lights go out

41:35.928 --> 41:38.844
♪ Let me feel I'm falling

41:38.887 --> 41:42.151
♪ I am falling safely

41:42.195 --> 41:46.416
♪ To the ground

41:46.460 --> 41:48.462
♪

41:48.506 --> 41:51.509
[vocalizing]
